				&nbsp;<br /><a name="112975049546934536"></a> 
				The universal doc comment was amusing. ODF can't even transform the Office XML formats w/o loss of information which is probably the primary value of the Office XML formats (being able to move legacy binary formats to fully documented XML formats w/o data loss).<BR/><BR/>I'm still waiting to see what hoops MA is going to jump through to get complex legacy documents into ODF without loss of data and/or time and money that could've been avoided if they allowed Office XML. I see another Munich Linux migration-styled mishap.<BR/><BR/>I do think MS should consider formalizing the Office XML and XPS Reach formats with ISO after they finalize the specs. I personally have no issue with the current licensing, but going to ISO would allow them to have a base standard everyone could use as a common denominator for interchange while allowing them to continue making further enhancements to their formats for future releases, much like they're doing currently with .NET and the CLI, C#, C++/CLI standards and Adobe w/ PDF. Maybe this has already been considered though, and they are waiting for final specs before submission.<br />
